<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,331,764,788]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name derived from the Latin word 
<emphasis box="[871,963,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">purpura</emphasis>
, which means purple, and the suffix 
<emphasis box="[1374,1429,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">-fera</emphasis>
, which means present. This refers to the purple shining at the anal margin of the forewing.
</paragraph>
